snippet: Initial reports said the three teenagers, one with American citizenship, were last heard from on Thursday on their way to a hitchhiking area south of Jerusalem.
abstract: Three Israeli teenagers missing in the West Bank are presumed to have been kidnapped; episode tests Israel's already strained ties with Palestinians and prompts involvement of State Dept amid reports that one of the teenagers is American.

byline.contributor: Said Ghazali contributed reporting from Jerusalem and Nayef Hashlamoun from Hebron, West Bank.

lead_paragraph: Initial reports said the three teenagers, one with American citizenship, were last heard from on Thursday on their way to a hitchhiking area south of Jerusalem.

headline.main: Israeli Teenagers Said to Be Kidnapped in West Bank
headline.print_headline: Israeli Teenagers Said to Be Kidnapped in West Bank
